  Systemd.service(5) - System and service manager
  Systemd.service(5)

  1. Description

  Systemd is a system and service manager for Linux, compatible with
  SysV and LSB init scripts. systemd provides aggressive parallelism
  and uses a micro-service approach, with systemd units as the basic
  building blocks of an application.

  Systemd is a replacement for sysvinit. It can be used to control the
  systemd process itself, as well as other processes. It is used to
  configure and manage the boot process and system lifetime, including
  start-up and shutdown of daemons and other services. Systemd is
